Imagine a spinning top that always lands with its tip pointing north when you measure its orientation. If the top is in an eigenstate of "north-pointing," measuring its direction will always give "north." But if it’s spinning chaotically (a superposition), the measurement might randomly give "north," "south," or anything in between.  

